ile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-830e413.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-830e413.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1112%2C740 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-830e413.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1668%2C1111 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-830e413.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=2224%2C1481 4x\"><img data-src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-830e413.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=620%2C413\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Pirelli P Zero Race Classic clincher tyre\" title=\"Pirelli P Zero Race Classic clincher tyre\" src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-830e413.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=620%2C413\"></picture></div><meta itemprop=\"url\" content=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-830e413.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=768%2C574\"><meta itemprop=\"width\" content=\"768\"><meta itemprop=\"height\" content=\"574\"></div><div><p>Published: <time datetime=\"2021-03-15T13:30:51+00:00\">March 15, 2021 at 1:30 pm</time></p><meta itemprop=\"datePublished\" content=\"2021-03-15T13:30:51+00:00\"><meta itemprop=\"dateModified\" content=\"2021-03-15T13:31:05+00:00\"><p></p></div></div><section itemprop=\"articleBody\"><p>Pirelli has today launched a new generation of its P Zero road tyre range, with two new clincher tyres that replace its highly rated <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/reviews/components/tyres/pirelli-pzero-velo-road-tyre-review/\">P Zero Velo clincher tyre</a>: the P Zero Race and P Zero Road.</p><p>Following the recent launch of the tubeless-ready <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/news/pirelli-p-zero-race-tlr/\">P Zero Race TLR and P Zero Race TLR SL tyres</a>, the P Zero Race uses Pirelli’s latest SmartEVO rubber compound, which has been tested by its sponsored <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/pro-bike/2021-worldtour-bikes/\">WorldTour teams</a> – AG2R Citroën, Trek-Segafredo and Team BikeExchange.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/brand/pirelli/\">Pirelli</a> says this compound combines three different polymers to ensure a “perfect balance of opposing characteristics, such as grip and rolling resistance”, though no specific figures for rolling resistance have been provided.</p><p>The P Zero Race tyre also uses a new 120 TPI (threads per inch) casing designed around an updated 19c rim – as per the latest <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/news/is-this-the-new-schwalbe-pro-one/\">ETRTO rim standards</a>.</p><p>This means the tyre will measure stated size on a rim with an 19mm internal width, and correspondingly smaller or larger on a narrower or wider rim (because of how the internal width of a rim affects the actual size of a tyre when inflated – wider rims tend to increase inflated tyre size, and vice versa).</p><h2>Pirelli P Zero Race clincher details and specifications</h2><div><picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-Version-b4374df.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=298%2C199, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-Version-b4374df.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=598%2C399 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-Version-b4374df.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=898%2C599 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-Version-b4374df.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1198%2C799 4x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.