rsion-b4374df.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1110%2C740 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-Version-b4374df.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1666%2C1111 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-Version-b4374df.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=2221%2C1481 4x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-Version-b4374df.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=555%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-Version-b4374df.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1110%2C740 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-Version-b4374df.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1666%2C1111 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-Version-b4374df.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=2221%2C1481 4x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><img data-src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-Version-b4374df.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=619%2C413\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Pirelli P Zero Race Classic clincher tyre\" title=\"Pirelli P Zero Race Classic Version\" src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/Pirelli-P-Zero-Race-Classic-Version-b4374df.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=619%2C413\"></picture></div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> Pirelli’s new P Zero Race clincher tyre is designed for racing, as the name suggests.</span></figcaption><p><span><i>Pirelli</i></span></p></div><p>The Pirelli P Zero Race clincher is a road racing tyre designed to offer a combination of low rolling resistance, high grip in both wet and dry conditions, and a comfortable ride quality.</p><p>As previously mentioned, it uses Pirelli’s latest SmartEVO rubber compound and the updated 120 TPI casing. A lightweight puncture protection belt is also incorporated into the casing, sitting centrally beneath the tread.</p><p>Available in three sizes, from 700 x 26c to 700 x 30c, and with a variety of side wall colours (including a ‘classic’ <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/tan-wall-tyres-hot-or-not/\">tan wall</a> option), Pirelli says the tyre is designed for performance and endurance use.</p><p>The Pirelli P Zero Race clincher is available now and has an RRP of £54.99 / €59.90 / $69.90.</p><div><p><i title=\"Enlarge photo\" data-slide-index=\"1\">Enlarge photo</i></p><div><picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 375px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 425px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 600px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 767px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 991px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(min-width: 992px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/P-ZERO-RACE-cross-section-bd6b222.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=960%2C640\" alt=\"Pirelli P Zero Race cross section\" height=\"640\" width=\"960\"></picture><div><p><i><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><title>icon / camera</title><g fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M10 12.08a1.6 1.6 0 1 1 0-3.204 1.6 1.6 0 0 1 0 3.204m0-4.457a2.856 2.856 0 0 0 0 5.711 2.856 2.856 0 0 0 0-5.71\" fill=\"#343434\"></path><path d=\"M16.036 13.23c0 .682-.553 1.234-1.234 1.234H5.199a1.234 1.234 0 0 1-1.234-1.234V7.623c0-.639.518-1.157 1.157-1.157h2.315l.11-.46a1.578 1.578 0 0 1 1.536-1.22h1.837c.734 0 1.37.505 1.537 1.22l.106.46h2.315c.64 0 1.158.518 1.158 1.157v5.607zM10 0C4.478 0 0 4.477 0 10s4.478 10 10 10c5.523 0 10-4.477 10-10S15.523 0 10 0z\" fill=\"#000\"></path></g></svg></i></p><figcaption><span>The P Zero Race clincher tyre uses a 120 TPI casing, with a lightweight puncture-protection belt beneath the tread.</span></figcaption><p><span><i>Pirelli</i></span></p></div></div></div><h3>Available sizes, colours and claimed weights</h3><ul><li>700 x 26c; black, classic, red, yellow, white; 205g</li><li>700 x 28c; black, classic, red, yellow, white; 225g</li><li>700 x 30c; black; 245g</li></ul><h2>Pirelli P Zero Road clincher details and specifications</h2><p>The P Zero Road clincher is more of an all-round road tyre.</p><p>It uses Pirelli’s EVO compound, which promises to offer better durability than the SmartEVO compound, on a 120 TPI casing, and focuses more on durability and high mileage. Pirelli says the tyre nevertheless offers “excellent grip and low rolling resistance”, though, again, no specific figures have been provided.</p><p>Curiously, the P Zero Road clincher tyre is designed around a narrower 17c rim. This means the tyre will measure true to its stated size on a rim with a 17mm internal width.</p><p>The P Zero Road clincher tyre is available now in three sizes, from 700 x 24c to 700 x 28c. It has an RRP of £37.99 / €39.90 / $49.90.</p><div><p><i title=\"Enlarge photo\" data-slide-index=\"1\">Enlarge photo</i></p><div><picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 375px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 425px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 600px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 767px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 991px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(min-width: 992px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/P-ZERO-Road-cross-section-bff4906.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=960%2C640\" alt=\"Pirelli P Zero Road cross section\" height=\"640\" width=\"960\"></picture><div><p><i><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><title>icon / camera</title><g fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M10 12.08a1.6 1.6 0 1 1 0-3.204 1.6 1.6 0 0 1 0 3.204m0-4.457a2.856 2.856 0 0 0 0 5.711 2.856 2.856 0 0 0 0-5.71\" fill=\"#343434\"></path><path d=\"M16.036 13.23c0 .682-.553 1.234-1.234 1.234H5.199a1.234 1.234 0 0 1-1.234-1.234V7.623c0-.639.518-1.157 1.157-1.157h2.315l.11-.46a1.578 1.578 0 0 1 1.536-1.22h1.837c.734 0 1.37.505 1.537 1.22l.106.46h2.315c.64 0 1.158.518 1.158 1.157v5.607zM10 0C4.478 0 0 4.477 0 10s4.478 10 10 10c5.523 0 10-4.477 10-10S15.523 0 10 0z\" fill=\"#000\"></path></g></svg></i></p><figcaption><span>The P Zero Road tyre uses Pirelli’s EVO compound that promises better durability.</span></figcaption><p><span><i>Pirelli</i></span></p></div></div></div><h3>Available sizes, colours and claimed weights</h3><ul><li>700 x 24c; black; 215g</li><li>700 x 26c; black; 235g</li><li>700 x 28c; black; 255g</li></ul></section><section><h3>Authors</h3><section><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/author/bromleysimon/\"><img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2020/06/Simon-Bromley_Profile-Pic_2020_04_12_IMG_4585-d34f7eb-scaled.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=60,60\" srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2020/06/Simon-Bromley_Profile-Pic_2020_04_12_IMG_4585-d34f7eb-scaled.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=120,120 120w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2020/06/Simon-Bromley_Profile-Pic_2020_04_12_IMG_4585-d34f7eb-scaled.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=60,60 60w,\" sizes=\"(max-width: 60px) 100vw, 60px\" width=\"60\" height=\"60\" alt=\"Simon Bromley_Profile Pic\" title=\"Simon Bromley_Profile Pic_2020_04_12_IMG_4585\"></a><p>Simon is a writer and photographer who has been riding bikes for fun since he was a kid. He took a deep dive into road racing, crits and time trial culture in his twenties, but as a person of very little talent, he always looks to tech to compensate. He loves nothing more than finding a smart (preferably cheap) hack that others hadn’t thought of. His stable of bikes isn’t the most extravagant, but they’re all customised to meet Simon’s particular tastes and kept fastidiously clean.</p></section></section></div>","author":"Simon Bromley","siteTitle":"BikeRadar","siteHash":"df99dd1320fcd97327a2def4c67247c08cd4090a7dab684a0eddb9b856f80ef1","entryHash":"1468027c31c24b01fe0fba68033aa506ee3cb044abf3a758ced68dcc4061240d","category":"Cycling"}